.TH FERM-NFT 1 "February 2026"
.SH NAME
ferm-nft \- firewall rule parser for iptables-nft
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ferm-nft
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIconfig files\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBferm-nft\fR is a Python implementation that parses firewall rules in ferm
syntax and generates iptables-nft commands. It provides the same configuration
syntax as the original ferm tool but uses the iptables-nft (netfilter) backend.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-noexec\fR
Do not execute, just show what would be done
.TP
\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-flush\fR
Flush all chains
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-lines\fR
Show all iptables commands
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-interactive\fR
Interactive mode - ask for confirmation
.TP
\fB\-t\fR \fITIMEOUT\fR, \fB\-\-timeout\fR \fITIMEOUT\fR
Timeout for interactive mode (seconds)
.TP
\fB\-\-remote\fR
Remote mode - ignore host-specific config
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Show version number
.TP
\fB\-\-slow\fR
Do not use iptables-restore
.TP
\fB\-\-shell\fR
Generate shell script
.TP
\fB\-\-domain\fR \fI{ip|ip6}\fR
Process only the specified domain
.TP
\fB\-d\fR \fIDEFINE\fR, \fB\-\-def\fR \fIDEFINE\fR
Override a variable (e.g., "$name=value")
.TP
\fB\-\-noflush\fR
Do not flush existing rules when restoring
.TP
\fB\-\-use-legacy\fR
Use iptables-legacy instead of iptables-nft
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE FORMAT
ferm-nft uses the same configuration syntax as ferm. Example:
.PP
.nf
.RS
table filter {
    chain INPUT {
        policy DROP;
        mod state state (ESTABLISHED RELATED) ACCEPT;
        interface lo ACCEPT;
        proto tcp dport ssh ACCEPT;
    }
    chain OUTPUT policy ACCEPT;
}
.RE
.fi
